               <p>WILLIAM ASHTON. I am a Police-constable. The<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183001140065"></xptr>prisoner was given into my charge on Saturday, the 2nd of January, for stealing a loaf of bread; I took her to the watch-house, and found on her two plumes of black feathers, and the next morning I found four handkerchiefs in a piece; she confessed she stole them from Mr. 
               <persName id="t18300114-124-person860">
                  James 
                  Drew
               <interp inst="t18300114-124-person860" type="surname" value="Drew"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300114-124-person860" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300114-124-person860" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who is a <rs id="t18300114-124-viclabel671" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300114-124-victim859 t18300114-124-viclabel671"></join> in Bridge-street, and said she was in the habit of buying and selling such things.</p>
